<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-28-0565 </DOCNO><TEXT>We construct a g-loop vertex for fermions in terms of the Szegoe kerneland we study its connections with the g-vacuum, that is the startingpoint for the computation of multiloop amplitudes in a recently developedoperator formalism on arbitrary Riemann surfaces. The same constructionis then performed for the free bosonic theory, checking bosonizationof the free fermionic theory on an arbitrary Riemann surface.</TEXT></DOC>